<h1>Split Layout</h1>
<p>Seperates two blocks of content with a slider to change their size.</p>

<p><b>Note:</b> Split layout takes full dimensions of its parent element. Make sure it has width and/or height set to what you want.</p>

<p><b>Note 2:</b> Split layout reacts to resize changes automatically and will adjust its size.</p>

<p><b>Note 3:</b> Split layout monitors visibility of child blocks. Though, just some basic cases are included.</p>

<p><b>Note 4:</b> If some of the mechanics from note 2 and 3 fail, you manually want to update the split layout, do so by calling: <code>document.querySelector('#my-split-layout').update();</code></p>

<h2>Example</h2>

<div class="alert alert-secondary mx-0">
	<h4 class="alert-heading">Parameters</h4>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="form-group col-md-4">
			<label>Orientation</label>
			<div class="form-check">
				{{#radio-button value="horizontal" groupValue=orientation changed="orientationChanged"}}Horizontal{{/radio-button}}
				{{#radio-button value="vertical" groupValue=orientation changed="orientationChanged"}}Vertical{{/radio-button}}
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="form-group col-md-4">
			<label for="paramPosition">Position</label>
			{{input value=position class="form-control" id="paramPosition"}}
		</div>
		<div class="form-group col-md-4">
			<label for="paramLimit">Limit [px]</label>
			{{input value=limit class="form-control" id="paramLimit"}}
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div style="height: 350px; border: 1px solid #000;">
	{{#split-layout orientation=orientation position=position limit=limit}}
		<div style="background-color: #fff3cd">First Block</div>
		<div style="background-color: #d1ecf1;">Second Block</div>
	{{/split-layout}}
</div>

